The '''Sulawesi pygmy woodpecker''' ('''''Yungipicus temminckii'''''), also known as the '''Sulawesi woodpecker''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Picidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to [[Sulawesi]] in [[Indonesia]].  Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical moist [[mountain]]s. Some taxonomic authorities continue to place this species in the genus ''[[Dendrocopos]]'' or ''[[Picoides]]''.

